The paper discusses the concept of crowd wisdom and its accuracy in making judgments. It also develops a theoretical framework for examining the conditions under which a crowd will be wise. The paper's focus on human judgment and decision-making suggests that it is likely to belong to the Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's emphasis on the accuracy of crowd judgments and the need for diversity among group members suggests that it could also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY), Systems and Control (cs.SD), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
